---
title: Open Guilds
---
<nav class="navigation">
  <ul>
    <li class="logo"><%=image_tag "open-guilds-logo.png" %>penGuilds</li>
    <li><%= link_to 'Docs', 'http://docs.openguilds.com/' %>
    <li><%= link_to 'Sign up', 'https://dashboard.openguilds.com/users/sign_up/' %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'Sign in', 'https://dashboard.openguilds.com/users/sign_in/' %></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<section class="main">
  <section class="segment" id="hero">
    <section class="copy">
      <h1>
      Create digital on-demand
      workforces that can do
      anything
      </h1>

      <p>
      OpenGuilds helps you build and manage online organizations that perform work
      online for rewards you set.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="links">
      <%= link_to 'Sign Up', '#', class: 'primary-button' %>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="segment">
    <figure>
      <%= image_tag 'community.png' %>
    </figure>

    <section class="copy">
      <h1>
      Build a community
      </h1>

      <p>
      Guilds have different tasks and levels of responsibility.
      When you set up your guild, you control the flow of work.
      </p>

      <p>
      Guilds can even use other platforms such as
      <strong>Amazon Mechanical Turk</strong> to provide an already
      existing community of workers you can have do the initial work that can
      be checked by more trusted members.
      </p>

    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="segment">
    <figure>
      <%= image_tag 'send-work.png' %>
    </figure>

    <section class="copy">
      <h1>
      Send work in
      </h1>

      <p>
      Upload your initial work to be done and have it assigned to available members
      of your guild.
      </p>

      <p>
      Guilds have an API developers can send data to. You can read more about
      our documentation <%= link_to 'here', 'http://docs.openguilds.com' %>
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="segment">
    <figure>
      <%= image_tag 'get-work.png' %>
    </figure>

    <section class="copy">
      <h1>
      Get finished work back
      </h1>

      <p>
      When the work is completed, we send it back to your service.
      </p>

      <p>
      Workers are rewarded for completing the tasks correctly.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</section>

<footer>
  <ul>
    <li><%= link_to 'Docs', 'http://docs.openguilds.com/' %>
    <li><%= link_to 'Sign up', 'https://dashboard.openguilds.com/users/sign_up/' %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'Sign in', 'https://dashboard.openguilds.com/users/sign_in/' %></li>

    <li><%= link_to 'Facebook', '#' %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'Pricing', '#' %></li>
  </ul>
</footer>
